I suffer from seasonal winter depression. I’ve had this for as long as I can remember. It comes, and it goes. I think of it as the night, it will eventually end, and the sun will come out. 

I now know what triggers it. 

It took me 25 years to realize staying cooped up too much leads to cabin fever. I honestly blame the weather for it. It’s always so cold and gloomy around this time of the year and I never feel like going out. 

But whenever I go out, I feel better. I’m reminded of how beautiful Mother Nature is and how she changes her colors for us during this challenging time. 

It’s fascinating to me how all the colors she changes into during  fall & winter, like; yellow ochre, coral, tangerine, orange ginger, terracotta, tan, brown, and so many more, all have a positive color psychology. These colors are associated with warmness, comfort and positivity. 

I truly believe, colors are forms of non-verbal communication that can speak volumes in a fraction of a second. 

So this is my camera roll lately. 

Ps, Did I miss out on a color? 🌈

Pumping myself with serotonin while I free-hand paint @lavashaklovers candies. I’m obsessed with how they taste. Makes the painting process even better 🍬 
 
Using: @princetonbrush @winsorandnewton

Getting ready to start painting tomorrow, but first, I need to refill the palette today because I want to put in a lot of layers, and I don’t want the paint to be too pigmented. Do you know what I mean?

I was feeling nostalgic and missing my home in Pakistan a bit too much today. So I recreated the room I had decorated before leaving the country. I miss the comfort of my room, and I miss my Amma. So many things which I want to say to her, and today, I felt like expressing them through my art. 

Most of you have lived through this moment with me. Who remembers this corner? 

#7uppakistan #DilKiBaat #7upKeSaath @7uppakistan

Ready for 2023! I'm still learning, let's learn together ♥️

Almost there!! 😆 

This year threw a lot of curve balls my way! It was a topsy-turvy year, but it was needed for where I’m headed next!

Imagination is the base of creation. Creativity is just piecing things together. 🦩🫖🫕🪭📚✨🍫

As artists, we often get caught up in trying to please a specific audience. We are constantly haunted by the looming question - Will they even like what we make? 

This constant worry can block our natural creativity and even lead to burnout. 

You might wonder, how can we get tired of something we love? It’s simple - we start making things for others, not for ourselves. 

Some say the best art is made when you’re true to yourself, like giving a gift to the world. You create what feels right in the moment. Later, you might find that people love it precisely because it was genuine and real.

Arguably, this kind of art vibrates on a higher frequency and it’s feels like an echo of our authentic voice. 

#theCreativeAct #basmahmasood #rickrubin #watercolors

Sunday was such a wholesome day! I spent it in the park making art with a bunch of cool folks. We were all there to let our creativity loose, and it felt really easy and natural. 

We were all busy making our own art, sharing laughs, munching on snacks, listening to some really good music and getting visits from cute puppies. Believe it or not, some pups even left cute paw prints on our paint!

But I think the highlight of the day was when two sweet little girls also joined us and made art with their parents. It made me so happy that we could make everyone feel safe and welcome.

This day was really good for @maaheem.and.music & I. We liked it so much that we’re probably going to do it again, and y’all are welcome to join us! 

Until then, keep making cool stuff 🥰💖

I wanted to show y’all my latest project that has been a true labor of love! Combining my passions for conceptualizing, directing, shooting, and editing, this project allowed me to stretch my creative wings and soar. 

Let me introduce you to Meadow - a brand that’s run by women, for women. Crafting unique intimates, Meadow is designed to support women at different stages of their lives. Whether it’s dealing with the aftermath of breast cancer, enduring painful pregnancies, or recovering from sports injuries, Meadow’s products are designed with a deep understanding of women’s needs. It’s truly a brand that has emerged out of necessity and empathy.

I’m incredibly grateful to @meadowforall for entrusting me with the creative freedom to bring their vision to life in the San Francisco Bay Area. As a content creator, there’s nothing more exhilarating than working on a project that resonates with my own values and allows me to showcase my skillset.

I’d love to know if you or any women in your life have felt the need for intimates that cater specifically to your needs at different life stages. It’s a cause that hits close to home for me and I’m thrilled to be part of a project that addresses it.

A special shoutout to the stunning @sheermakinglight , who breathed life into our vision and made this video possible. 

#basmahmasood #basmahmasoodfilms #sanfranciscovideographer

Seeing how people live in beautiful ways deeply affects how we think and dream. I think it makes us want to explore life’s diverse experiences and celebrate the uniqueness of human existence. Just by keeping an open heart and a curious mind, we usually begin a journey to discover ourselves and the world around us, guided by the beauty we have witnessed.

This is my new favorite illustration, likely the best I've ever created so far. It took me over 10 hours to complete, but the effort was entirely worthwhile!

It reflects what's going on inside my brain these days 🛸🌏🍓🌙🎸🎵

I recently had the honor of working with @babosconceptkitchen on something truly special.   Have you ever tried Panjiri?   It’s this incredibly wholesome treat, reminiscent of granola but even healthier and gluten-free. But more than its taste, it’s the story behind it that touched my heart. 
Babo shared how, for generations, the women in her family bonded over the making of Panjiri. It became a space for conversations, decisions, and shared life experiences. Her mother’s voice note about the labor of love that goes into making Panjiri reminded me so much of my own grandma and how food was also such a powerful connector for her too. I guess that’s why I poured so much into this video. And trust me, once you try Panjiri, you’ll be hooked! I finished my bag in one go. 😅 
Want to try? Order now at www.babos-kitchen.com/panjiri  
P.S. Let me know what you think of the video! Shot, directed, and edited by yours truly ♥️

When I see the morning sun come up, it feels so special to me. Everything looks golden and bright, and it just lifts my mood. That early sunlight gives me hope and makes me feel better. It’s like watching the world wake up, and it makes me believe anything is possible.

“People can live a hundred years without really living for a minute.” - Gilmore Girls

Snapped an amazing picture of the moon last night using my brother’s telescope. The cool part? The camera wasn’t even fixed to the telescope—We had to hold it steady! The earth kept turning and we kept getting blurred shot until we got a good one. 
The moon was so bright it was almost blinding. Took me a few minutes to recalibrate my eyes to look at the stars again. And then to our surprise we also spotted Saturn with its rings and Jupiter with its 3 moons. Sadly we couldn’t get a good photograph of it. 

Sigh! I’m always in awe of the cosmos. 

Now I’m really excited about taking more photos of the sky. Just need to figure out how to afford all that fancy gear! 😂
